---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="FraiseQL vs Hasura - Detailed Comparison"
  description="Compare FraiseQL (compile-time) vs Hasura (runtime introspection). Understand the trade-offs and when to choose each."
>
  <div style="padding: 2rem; max-width: 1280px; margin: 0 auto;">
    <h1>FraiseQL vs Hasura</h1>
    <p style="font-size: 1.1rem; color: #666;">
      Two fundamentally different approaches to GraphQL.
    </p>

    <section style="margin: 3rem 0;">
      <h2>The Core Difference</h2>
      <table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 1rem 0;">
        <tr style="background: #f5f3ff;">
          <th style="padding: 1rem; text-align: left; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;"></th>
          <th style="padding: 1rem; text-align: center; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;">FraiseQL</th>
          <th style="padding: 1rem; text-align: center; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;">Hasura</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td style="padding: 1rem; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;"><strong>Philosophy</strong></td>
          <td style="padding: 1rem; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;">Compile-time optimization (build time)</td>
          <td style="padding: 1rem; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;">Runtime introspection (per request)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="background: #fafafa;">
          <td style="padding: 1rem; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;"><strong>Schema Source</strong></td>
          <td style="padding: 1rem; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;">Explicit: Python/TypeScript decorators</td>
          <td style="padding: 1rem; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;">Automatic: Database introspection</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td style="padding: 1rem; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;"><strong>Query Planning</strong></td>
          <td style="padding: 1rem; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;">Pre-computed at compile time</td>
          <td style="padding: 1rem; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;">Determined per request at runtime</td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="background: #fafafa;">
          <td style="padding: 1rem; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;"><strong>Performance</strong></td>
          <td style="padding: 1rem; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;">More predictable, primarily bound by database</td>
          <td style="padding: 1rem; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;">Variable, depends on query complexity and schema</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td style="padding: 1rem; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;"><strong>N+1 Prevention</strong></td>
          <td style="padding: 1rem; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;">Prevented by compiler analysis</td>
          <td style="padding: 1rem; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;">Addressed via batching and caching</td>
        </tr>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 3rem 0;">
      <h2>When to Choose Hasura</h2>
      <ul style="font-size: 1.05rem;">
        <li>
          <strong>Rapid prototyping</strong> – Schema changes without recompilation
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Small teams</strong> – No build infrastructure needed
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>PostgreSQL-only</strong> – Hasura's primary strength
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Admin interfaces</strong> – Instant GraphQL for CRUD operations
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Schema-driven development</strong> – Let database schema drive API
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Non-critical systems</strong> – Where performance variance is acceptable
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p style="margin-top: 1rem; padding: 1rem; background: #f0fdf4; border-left: 4px solid #059669; border-radius: 4px;">
        <strong>✅ Good Fit:</strong> Startups prototyping features, internal dashboards, CMS backends, small REST APIs being converted to GraphQL.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 3rem 0;">
      <h2>When to Choose FraiseQL</h2>
      <ul style="font-size: 1.05rem;">
        <li>
          <strong>Production performance</strong> – Need deterministic, predictable behavior
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Regulated industries</strong> – Healthcare (HIPAA), finance (SOC 2), government (FedRAMP)
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Auditability</strong> – 100% mutation trail required for compliance
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Multi-database</strong> – PostgreSQL, MySQL, SQLite, SQL Server from one schema
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Analytics workloads</strong> – Large result sets, complex aggregations, Arrow Flight streaming
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Ecosystem approach</strong> – Want 11 tools that work together vs. one tool
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p style="margin-top: 1rem; padding: 1rem; background: #fef2f2; border-left: 4px solid #dc2626; border-radius: 4px;">
        <strong>✅ Good Fit:</strong> Banking APIs, healthcare platforms, SaaS with compliance requirements, multi-database deployments, data warehousing APIs.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 3rem 0;">
      <h2>Technical Comparison</h2>

      <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Performance</h3>
      <p>
        <strong>FraiseQL:</strong> Query execution time ~1-2ms per request (deterministic, pre-optimized SQL)
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Hasura:</strong> Query execution time ~5-15ms per request (includes introspection, planning, execution per request)
      </p>
      <p style="margin-top: 1rem; color: #666;">
        <em>Trade-off: Hasura's slower per-request time allows instant schema updates. FraiseQL's faster time requires deployment for schema changes.</em>
      </p>

      <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Auditability</h3>
      <p>
        <strong>FraiseQL:</strong> 100% mutation trail – Every mutation is logged, cryptographically signed, immutable. Field-level encryption on sensitive data. Required for HIPAA/SOC 2.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Hasura:</strong> Partial audit trail via events – Can log mutations via webhooks, but not built-in cryptographic signing or immutable logs.
      </p>

      <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">N+1 Query Prevention</h3>
      <p>
        <strong>FraiseQL:</strong> Impossible to write N+1 queries – The compiler generates optimal SQL joins. Batching at query boundary only.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Hasura:</strong> Mitigates N+1 via batching and caching – Can still occur if not careful. Remote joins can amplify N+1 issues.
      </p>

      <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Schema Evolution</h3>
      <p>
        <strong>FraiseQL:</strong> Schema changes require recompilation and deployment. Enables breaking change detection via CI/CD. Zero-downtime deployments via blue/green (fraisier).
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Hasura:</strong> Schema changes are live immediately. No breaking change detection. Easier for rapid development, risky for production.
      </p>

      <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Multi-Database Support</h3>
      <p>
        <strong>FraiseQL:</strong> One schema compiles to SQL for PostgreSQL, MySQL, SQLite, SQL Server. Query execution adapts per database.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Hasura:</strong> PostgreSQL only. Data federation can query other databases but with higher latency (Remote Joins).
      </p>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 3rem 0;">
      <h2>Real-World Scenarios</h2>

      <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Scenario: Healthcare Platform (HIPAA)</h3>
      <p>
        <strong>Requirements:</strong> Strong consistency, 100% audit trail, field-level encryption, SOC 2 compliance.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Hasura:</strong> ❌ Difficult. Would need external audit logging system, encryption middleware. Not designed for regulatory compliance.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>FraiseQL:</strong> ✅ Built-in. Audit logging, field-level encryption, deterministic execution, compliance-ready.
      </p>

      <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Scenario: Startup MVP (Ship in 2 Weeks)</h3>
      <p>
        <strong>Requirements:</strong> Fast development, schema changes daily, learning as we go.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Hasura:</strong> ✅ Perfect. GraphQL on day 1, instant schema changes, no build pipeline.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>FraiseQL:</strong> ❌ Slower. Need to set up build pipeline, learn compilation model, pre-define schema.
      </p>

      <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Scenario: Large Analytics Dashboard (1GB Result Sets)</h3>
      <p>
        <strong>Requirements:</strong> Memory efficiency, streaming results, 40% data compression.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Hasura:</strong> ❌ Difficult. Would need custom batching and compression. Each request buffers full result set.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>FraiseQL:</strong> ✅ Built-in. fraiseql-wire (200K× memory efficiency), Arrow Flight (25-40% compression), streaming transport.
      </p>

      <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Scenario: Multi-Tenant SaaS (PostgreSQL + MySQL Tenants)</h3>
      <p>
        <strong>Requirements:</strong> Support multiple database backends per tenant.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Hasura:</strong> ❌ Can't do natively. Would need separate Hasura instances per database type.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>FraiseQL:</strong> ✅ One schema compiles to all database types. Dynamic tenant routing at runtime.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 3rem 0;">
      <h2>Migration Path (Hasura → FraiseQL)</h2>
      <p>
        If you're using Hasura and want to migrate to FraiseQL:
      </p>
      <ol>
        <li>
          <strong>Extract schema</strong> – Hasura's introspected schema → FraiseQL Python/TypeScript decorators
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Compile</strong> – Use fraiseql-cli to generate optimized SQL and schema.compiled.json
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Test queries</strong> – Verify query results match Hasura's
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Blue/green deploy</strong> – Use fraisier to orchestrate zero-downtime switch
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Decommission Hasura</strong> – Remove runtime introspection layer
        </li>
      </ol>
      <p style="margin-top: 1rem;">
        <strong>Typical effort:</strong> 2-4 weeks depending on schema complexity and custom resolvers.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 3rem 0;">
      <h2>Honest Tradeoffs</h2>
      <table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 1rem 0;">
        <tr style="background: #f5f3ff;">
          <th style="padding: 1rem; text-align: left; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;">Dimension</th>
          <th style="padding: 1rem; text-align: center; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;">FraiseQL Advantage</th>
          <th style="padding: 1rem; text-align: center; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;">Hasura Advantage</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td style="padding: 1rem; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;"><strong>Performance</strong></td>
          <td style="padding: 1rem; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;">✅ 5-10× faster</td>
          <td style="padding: 1rem; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;">Easy iteration</td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="background: #fafafa;">
          <td style="padding: 1rem; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;"><strong>Development Speed</strong></td>
          <td style="padding: 1rem; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;">Build system overhead</td>
          <td style="padding: 1rem; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;">✅ No build needed</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td style="padding: 1rem; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;"><strong>Compliance Ready</strong></td>
          <td style="padding: 1rem; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;">✅ Built-in HIPAA/SOC2</td>
          <td style="padding: 1rem; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;">Requires custom work</td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="background: #fafafa;">
          <td style="padding: 1rem; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;"><strong>Database Flexibility</strong></td>
          <td style="padding: 1rem; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;">✅ 4 databases</td>
          <td style="padding: 1rem; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;">PostgreSQL only</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td style="padding: 1rem; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;"><strong>Ecosystem</strong></td>
          <td style="padding: 1rem; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;">✅ 11 integrated tools</td>
          <td style="padding: 1rem; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;">Plugin system</td>
        </tr>
      </table>
    </section>

    <p style="margin-top: 3rem;">
      <a href="/vs">← Back to Comparisons</a> | <a href="/">Home</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
